#Win11 Setup with local account/without internet
#Disconnect from internet
#press Shift + F10 on the "Let's connect you to a network" screen to open Command Prompt.
OOBE\BYPASSNRO and press Enter
#computer will reboot. "I dont have internet" will now be an option

https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/answers/questions/1486646/how-to-set-windows-10-autologin

#Auto login:
#Open Regedit
HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\Winlogon
New string: AutoAdminLogon
Value: 1
New string: DefaultUserName
Value: username
New string: DefaultPassword
Value: password


#Force close on restart/shutdown/logout:
#Open Regedit
HKEY_USERS\.DEFAULT\Control Panel\Desktop
AutoEndTasks String value
#0 = Off
#1 = On

#Delete mapped drive
#open cmd as admin
net use Z: /delete

#Delete all mapped drive
#open cmd as admin
net use * /delete

#Diable auto update
#Open GPedit
gpedit.msc
Computer Configuration > Administrative Templates > Windows Components > Windows Update > Manage end user experience, and set the Configure Automatic Updates
